  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal Profile)",
  "description": "This unit of assurance documents the credibility evidence for a CFD-based hemolysis prediction model applied to the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump. The model has been applied in clinical research contexts to inform ventricular assist device design decisions, where absolute hemolysis index predictions are compared against bench-top experimental measurements. Thirteen credibility factors are evaluated under ASME V&V 40-2018 at a nominal model risk level consistent with Class III device applications. Monte Carlo uncertainty propagation was performed across key rheological and geometric input parameters. Seven factors were formally assessed; six were scoped as not-assessed due to data availability constraints. The overall credibility evidence package is submitted under the Minimal conformance profile; structured context-of-use scope is conveyed through narrative rather than a formal ContextOfUse record.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou2-hemolysis-prediction",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou2-hemolysis-cfd-credible",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-centrifugal-pump-cfd-hemolysis-v2",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-experimental-hemolysis-dataset",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/morrison-monte-carlo-uq-runs-2024"
  ],
